metadata.name: DEPRESSLAND - TheFEARZ #15
metadata.description:
Don´t have FOMO - FEARZ are here!

THE FEARZ UNIVERSE
A universe of over 10.000 NFTs - unique digital collectibles

There are 5 countries on the FEARZ Planet and one of them is DEPRESSLAND.
In DEPRESSLAND it is very dangerous, something is constantly exploding and you always have to be on your guard. As a result, all FEARZ here live in a depressed mood a permanent, deep sense of exhaustion and a complete lack of joy and interest in the world. Everyone here suffers from persistent insomnia because they are constantly afraid for their lives.

There will be 5 drops, one every two weeks for each country on the FEARZ planet.
(LOST ANGELES, PAINDAMIC, DEPRESSLAND, FRUSTRATIA, PANIC HILLS)

Whoever holds an NFT from each country on Saturday, 10th of Sep is qualified and receives a SPECIAL AIRDROP PACK!

metadata.name: Growth v02 #292
metadata.description:
Growth patterns, version 2. January 2022
Edition of 512

Growth v02 is an generative exploration of patterns in the style of William Morris' iconic wallpaper designs from the 1800s. The code for the Growth series was originally designed to create plausible road networks but has been rewritten to create more organic curved forms. Created with p5js.

'space' to pause the simulation
'h' to toggle to higher res (increases canvas size but runs slower: great for screengrabs)
'r' to reset the seed (some features are locked to the original hash)
's' to save an image to disk
All generated patterns are tile-able horizontally and vertically.

Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

This project relies heavily on randomly generated values. It has been thoroughly tested. However, there is always the chance that the wrong combination of randomness can create less-compelling growth. If you feel you version is not living up to the potential promised with this piece, please email me.

metadata.name: DisOrder #185
metadata.description:
Manual Dutch Auction (DA): 84 · 56 · 38 · 26 · 18  every 8 minutes.
Auction will stop changing price when non-reserves are fully minted.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////

All that is, starts with Order.

Order attempts to evade entropy by following its own intrinsic patterns. Then, inevitably, there is change: an anomaly, a nudge that turns into a catalyst for widespread change.The momentum cannot be stopped.

Brief cycles build upon themselves, iterating and breaking into something new with each turn. Now, looking back, the accumulation of small divergences look like a leap, with trails of evolutionary decline casting tall shadows on the patterns that bore them.

The beauty of what this entropy creates, rises beyond chaos. It represents the past, and signals the future, and suddenly looks like a wild take on Order itself – the true DisOrder of life.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////

FEATURES :
21 Features implemented including colors, styles, technical parameters...

INTERACTIVITY :
Press ‘h’ in live mode for a list of options.
Press 's' to save an image of the output at the current resolution
Press ‘1’-’9’ to increase resolution
...

metadata.name: Toccata #249
metadata.description:
Toccata is a piece about decay, about the impermanent. The emergence over time or, rather, progression of entropy is a key characteristic of our universe. Everything evolves to nothing. We as mortal beings have sometimes trouble reconciling with this idea. Humans have sought immortality for millennia, be it through ancient potions or modern medicine, be it from leaving a legacy that we feel will stand the test of time. It will, only to decay later than us.

Toccata is a piece about change. Change lies at the heart of human cognition and human nature. Our thoughts and our emotions happen over time, and are a function of the change that is both around us and at the very core of our selves. Change comes in nature in cycles. Seasons of growth, seasons of ripe fruits of life, seasons of decay, of death, rebirth.

Toccata is music. We find music to convey some of the deepest streams of human condition, connecting it to some other form of being. Music also happens over time, and music happens because of change. Music encodes our feelings better than any other aid we may have. Toccata incorporates this at its very core, as the main sound is Andreas' family piano where he learned to play, sampled this past July.

Read more about the piece, and the collaboration between Marcelo and Andreas on andreasrau.eu/toccata

---

Basic controls:
- Click on the piece or press spacebar to start it (WebAudio requires user intervention for the music to start). Once the music has started, again click or press spacebar to play/pause.
- Press “s” to save a still at the current resolution
- Press “r” to start recording a video at the current resolution, then “r” again to stop.

---

WebM audio-video recording performed using the library RecordRTC by https://muazkhan.com/, MIT licence.

metadata.name: Medusa #45
metadata.description:
“Nunc, o fortissime, fare, precor, Perseu, quanta virtute quibusque artibus abstuleris crinita draconibus ora!” - Ovid, Metamorphoses Book IV 769
"Perseus, I beg you to tell us by what prowess and by what arts you carried off that head with snakes for hair."

Medusa is built in 3D with p5.js using physics of oimo.js (see LICENSE.md). 

For high resolution renderings (4x resolution of current canvas size): Open the artwork in its own browser tab, add the parameter '&highres=4' to the url and reload. e.g. https://gateway.fxhash2.xyz/ipfs/<something>/?fxhash=ooXrQmk42nyJd4HAB63v7jJ9R27DiwcbwDaUEYuX3FvGDzfwNog&highres=4 .

For endless waves: Open the artwork in its own browser tab, add the parameter '&infinity=true' to the url and reload. e.g. https://gateway.fxhash2.xyz/ipfs/<something>/?fxhash=ooXrQmk42nyJd4HAB63v7jJ9R27DiwcbwDaUEYuX3FvGDzfwNog&infinity=true .

For an export as .PNG press 'e'.

I am afraid that's all there is to say.

Stefan Schwaha, @sektionschef, https://digitalitility.com/

metadata.name: Возвышение #60
metadata.description:
Возвышение (Eng.: Elevation) is the next step of my study of Suprematism, textures and colours, partially inspired by Lazar Khidekel works. 
The work depicts the superiority of the simplest geometric forms and colours over everything else.

——————

Rendering takes around 20-30 seconds at 60 fps, might take longer on older devices.
Press [Arrow Up / Down] to increase / decrease drawing speed.
Press [1…6] to change an image resolution up to 10k.
Press [S] after the image is rendered to save it.

Created using p5.js.
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.
